ZH: 他拒绝承担任何责任。
EN: He refused to take any responsibility.

ZH: 只有你愿意承担风险，才能有所得。
EN: Only if you are willing to take risks can you gain something.

ZH: 我很荣幸能承担这个任务。
EN: I am honored to take on this task.

ZH: 她不愿意承担这么大的压力。
EN: She is not willing to bear such a heavy pressure.

ZH: 你愿意承担这份工作吗？
EN: Are you willing to take on this job?

ZH: 作为领导者，他必须承担更多的责任。
EN: As a leader, he must take on more responsibility.

ZH: 他决定承担决定的后果。
EN: He decided to accept the consequences of his decision.

ZH: 这个项目需要有人愿意承担领导角色。
EN: This project needs someone willing to take on a leadership role.

ZH: 这是一个需要团队共同承担的挑战。
EN: This is a challenge that needs to be tackled by the team collectively.

ZH: 他承担了损失的责任。
EN: He took responsibility for the loss.

ZH: 他没有勇气承担失败的可能性。
EN: He doesn't have the courage to face the possibility of failure.

ZH: 今天我要承担我的错误。
EN: Today I will take responsibility for my mistakes.

ZH: 她不愿意承担额外的工作。
EN: She is not willing to take on extra work.

ZH: 你能够承担这次旅行的花费吗？
EN: Can you afford to bear the cost of this trip?

ZH: 请不要让孩子承担太多的压力。
EN: Please don't let the children bear too much pressure.

ZH: 谁来承担这笔费用呢？
EN: Who will take on this expense?

ZH: 我们需要有人愿意承担风险。
EN: We need someone willing to take risks.

ZH: 这是我们的责任，我们必须承担。
EN: This is our responsibility, we must bear it.

ZH: 他勇于承担重大挑战。
EN: He is brave enough to take on major challenges.

ZH: 每个人都有自己承担的责任。
EN: Everyone has their own responsibilities to bear.
